# Cursor — BrightHive rules

Read AGENTS.md and PR_RULES.md (both at repo root) before generating code.

## Hard rules

- PR size: < 500 lines = good, 500–700 = warning, 700–900 = stop, ≥ 900 = blocked. Reviewers will refuse oversized PRs. See PR_RULES.md.
- No AI attribution in commits, comments, or files. No "Generated by Cursor".
- Specs first — no code without a spec at docs/specs/.
- Conventional commits: type(scope): description, imperative, ≤72 chars.
- Never log credentials, JWTs, OAuth tokens, or PII.

## When approaching limits

If your generated diff is hitting 400 lines, stop and ask the user whether to split. Don't unilaterally produce a 900+ line diff.

## Project-specific conventions

- Sprint artifacts at jira/sprint/{N}/ — never invent alternate paths
- Jira tickets need a parent epic via parent: {key: "BH-XXX"} (never customfield_10014)
- Trial/PoC tracker work uses scripts/poc_tracker/

When in doubt, mirror AGENTS.md and PR_RULES.md.
